Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Glyphosate in Ethanol + Water, 1-Propanol + Water, and 2-Propanol + Water from (293 to 333) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of glyphosate in water, ethanol + water, propan-1-ol + water, and propan-2-ol + water was measured by using a laser technique at temperatures from (293 to 333) K at a pressure of 0.1 MPa. The solubility of glyphosate in water and the binary mixtures increases with temperature and mole fraction of water. The solubility data were correlated with a semiempirical equation.
